	   <tr><td colspan=2>The time you want to use this is when chain casting pets.. your pet is about to die, so you cast another and when the casting bar is at the appropriate point you use Reclaim Energy to get rid of the first and get back a portion of the mana the new pet is costing you.. truly efficient..<br><br>I agree that charming is the better option where you have more than one of the mob you are killing. but that isnt always the case.. sometimes a cast pet is the best way to go.. especially with the higher level pets.<br><br>Stats on this arent much, but if you hunting with your pet, its a darn nice way to free a slot.. and who cares about int anyway? if im not mezzing in a group (or charming) i dont need a lot of cha and will have int to burn.. +2 int and +20 mana is fine.. its the effect that rocks here!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
